(Senior Fellow at the Competitive Enterprise Institute, where he writes on global warming, energy policy, and other public policy issues. Prior to joining CEI in April 2002, he served as Director of External Relations at the Reason Foundation in Los Angeles, California. During the 106th Congress, Marlo served as Staff Director of the House Government Reform Subcommittee on National Economic Growth, Natural Resources, and Regulatory Affairs; &amp;#34;EPA~’s Carbon Pollution Standard — One Step Closer to Policy Disaster,&amp;#34; http://www.globalwarming.org/2012/06/25/epas-carbon-pollution-standard-one-step-closer-to-policy-disaster/)&#xD;
&#xD;
